io.spine.server.storage.memory

Class RecordComparator<I,R extends com.google.protobuf.Message>

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.spine.server.storage.memory.RecordComparator<I,R>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.util.Comparator<RecordWithColumns<I,R>>

    public class RecordComparator<I,R extends com.google.protobuf.Message>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Comparator<RecordWithColumns<I,R>>, java.io.Serializable
    A comparator for sorting the contents of TenantRecords in a provided sorting order.
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
    Implementation Note:
    More sophisticated storage implementations can sort records by non-Comparable fields like message-type fields, depending on their storage method (e.g. comparing the string content of messages).The in-memory implementation stores all column values "as-is" and cannot do that. Trying to sort by column of non-comparable type will lead to an exception being thrown.
